installation of Miniconda

visit: https://conda.io/miniconda.html

Download linux Python 3.6, 64-bit version. 

Find location of downloaded file: which linux Python 3.6

Make sure all associated files are moved to Downloads folder: mv [specific linux python file name] Downloads

Then, within downloads folder set up the bioconda channels, type:
conda config --add channels defaults
conda config --add channels conda-forge
conda config --add channels bioconda

Then you are able to install available packages, type:
conda install -c bioconda bwa
conda install -c bioconda fastqc
conda install -c bioconda trim-galore


(used https://bioconda.github.io/ as a reference)
